quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  70,36,What is the matter with the faithless that they scramble toward you
  70,37,"from left and right, in groups"
  70,38,Does each man among them hope to enter the garden of bliss
  70,39,"Never! Indeed, We created them from what they know"
  70,40,So I swear by the Lord of the easts and the wests that We are able
  70,41,"to replace them with [others] better than them and We are not to be outmaneuvered"
  70,42,So leave them to gossip and play till they encounter the day they are promised
  70,43,"the day when they emerge from graves, hastening, as if racing toward a target"
  70,44,"with a humbled look [in their eyes], overcast by abasement. That is the day they had been promised"